The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 10 November is 1,053,330 (1,871.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 November, there were 138,005 new confirmed cases (245.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 October, there were 128,159 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 8% ( 9,846 extra cases).
